news.title: Hong Kong court dismisses bid to liquidate Country Garden
news.para: A Hong Kong court dismissed a petition to liquidate Chinese property giant Country Garden on Monday, weeks after the firm said it had restructured its massive offshore debt obligations. High Court judge Linda Chan took less than a minute on Monday to dismiss the petition, which was initiated in 2024 by Country Garden creditor Ever Credit Limited.

news.title: Bhopal: Lakeview Residency to be razed & rebuilt as five-star hotel
news.para: A consortium including Genex Hotels, Dilip Buildcon, and IHCL will redevelop the MPT Lake View Residency Hotel. The project aims to create a minimum 5-star property with a convention center. This development is expected to significantly boost Bhopal's tourism and its standing as a MICE destination.

news.title: Rajasthan government mulls relaxing building norms to boost investment
news.para: Rajasthan is considering relaxing building height and setback norms to foster industrial growth and affordable housing. The state aims to adopt a "everything is permitted unless prohibited" principle for land use, simplifying processes for businesses and individuals. These reforms, part of a national initiative, focus on reducing licensing, integrating approvals, and curbing litigation to enhance ease of doing business.

news.title: Co-operative societies' officials cannot decide flat succession disputes: Bombay HC
news.para: The Bombay High Court criticized the divisional joint registrar for overturning a membership grant to a housing society. Justice Amit Borkar stated the registrar overstepped jurisdiction by delving into succession disputes, which falls outside the scope of membership regulation. The court emphasized that a nominee's role is to facilitate dealings after a member's death, not to establish ownership.

news.title: Gurugram: Two farmhouses on 26 acres in the Raisina hill area in Aravalis razed
news.para: Forest officials demolished a concrete wall and two farmhouses in Gurugram's protected Aravali landscape after discovering fresh construction. The action, spanning 26 acres, followed inspections revealing unauthorized concretisation and use of earthmovers, violating the Aravali Notification of 1992.

news.title: Residents of new sectors in Gurugram protest against C&D waste plants
news.para: Residents of new sectors along Dwarka Expressway are protesting against the proposed establishment of two construction and demolition (C&D) waste processing plants in sectors 103 and 106. They argue the locations violate planning norms and pose health risks, demanding relocation away from housing clusters. Fencing has already begun at one site, escalating resident concerns.

news.title: YEIDA makes ₹389 crore from e-auction of plots near Noida airport
news.para: Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA) generated Rs 389 crore from an e-auction of three group housing plots, exceeding the reserve price by Rs 106 crore. This auction, part of a renewed allotment drive after 13 years, brings the total group housing plots allotted since 2024 to 11, anticipating the development of nearly 10,000 flats.

news.title: Mumbai's office space costs surged by 8% in Q4 2025
news.para: Mumbai's net effective office costs surged by 8.0% in Q4 2025, the highest globally, driven by limited supply and strong demand for Grade A spaces. Delhi also saw prime office cost increases, mirroring sustained occupier interest. Globally, prime office costs rose 1.1% quarterly and 5.1% annually, with India outperforming the global average.

news.title: Varanasi development body pushes group housing projects; nod to 474 layouts
news.para: Varanasi Development Authority's efforts to encourage planned colony development have led to the sanctioning of over 474 layouts. However, a significant concern has emerged as 73 group housing projects, completed before 2020 and occupied by residents, have failed to obtain completion certificates, raising safety and legal uncertainties.

news.title: Construction debris from 2,000 redevelopment projects in Mumbai ‘go missing’
news.para: A civic investigation revealed that construction debris from nearly 2,000 Mumbai redevelopment projects never reached designated disposal sites. Environmentalists suspect the waste was sold to the land mafia for encroaching on mangrove and wetland areas. The Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation has now halted further construction permissions until developers contract with official recycling plants.

news.title: Real estate jobs could approach 100 million by 2030: Report
news.para: India's real estate sector is set for significant growth. Employment is projected to reach 100 million by 2030. The market value is expected to surge to ₹88 trillion. This expansion will be driven by increasing urbanisation and supportive policy measures. The sector's contribution to GDP is also anticipated to rise substantially.

news.title: WeWork India leases 90,000 sq ft in Gurugram
news.para: WeWork India has launched a new 90,000 sq ft co-working space at Atrium Place in Gurugram's Udyog Vihar, adding over 1,200 desks to its NCR portfolio. This expansion, in partnership with DLF, marks WeWork India's 15th center in the region and contributes to a significant increase in enterprise desks.

news.title: Shriram Properties acquires four acres land in Bengaluru
news.para: Shriram Properties has bought four acres of land on Sarjapur Main Road in Bengaluru. The company plans a new high-rise residential project there. This development will offer about five lakh sq ft of saleable area. The project's gross development value is estimated at ₹550-600 crore. A launch is anticipated in late 2026. Shriram Properties also recently acquired Shrivision Upscale Spaces.

news.title: Five listed REITs distribute over ₹2,450 crore to 3.8 lakh unitholders in Q3 FY26
news.para: India's five listed REITs distributed over ₹2,450 crore to 3.8 lakh unitholders in Q3 FY26. These REITs manage a vast portfolio of prime office and retail spaces, having cumulatively distributed over ₹29,100 crore since their listings. The sector's growth is bolstered by strong leasing and occupancy, with policy proposals aiming to further enhance capital access and market depth.

news.title: Lead-to-buy cycle shrinks to 26 days in 2025; ₹2-3 crore homes sell fastest in 15 days
news.para: Despite a 14% dip in housing sales across top cities in 2025, the average time to convert a lead into a booking significantly shortened to 26 days. This improvement was primarily driven by quicker decision-making in higher ticket-size segments, particularly homes priced between ₹2 crore and ₹3 crore, which saw a conversion time of just 15 days.

news.title: Premium housing drives 50% of sales as affordable segment shrinks 17% in 2025: Report
news.para: India's housing market shifted towards expensive homes in 2025. Homes over one crore rupees made up half of all sales. Demand for cheaper homes fell significantly. Developers also launched fewer affordable housing projects. This indicates a major change in what buyers want and where builders focus their efforts.

news.title: Chamarajanagar drafts plan to declare 67 revenue villages
news.para: Chamarajanagar district is set to declare 67 more villages as revenue villages, a move that will bring development and government facilities to these settlements. This declaration will enable residents to obtain official property records, access loans, and receive other essential government benefits previously unavailable to them.

news.title: Keystone Realtors to redevelop eight housing societies in Andheri East, Mumbai
news.para: Keystone Realtors has secured a significant redevelopment project in Andheri (East), Mumbai, with an estimated gross development value of ₹1,775 crore. The project will redevelop Om Nagar Co-operative Housing Society Federation, comprising eight societies and covering over 20,569 sq metres. This initiative will provide rehabilitation for 637 members and unlock approximately five lakh sq ft of free-sale area.

news.title: Goa completes 25% of land records update
news.para: Goa state government is updating land records and issuing urban property cards. Around 25 percent of this work is complete. Initial public concerns about land mergers and property confiscation have been addressed. The survey aims to accurately record land ownership. The government targets completion by February, with potential extensions if needed. This initiative ensures clear property rights for all landowners.

news.title: Every land parcel in Delhi to geta 14-digit Aadhaar number
news.para: Delhi has launched Bhu Aadhaar, assigning a 14-digit Unique Land Parcel Identification Number (ULPIN) to every land parcel to modernize records and enhance accountability. This initiative aims to combat corruption and land disputes by creating a digital 'Aadhaar' for property ownership, ensuring greater transparency and streamlining transactions.
